<p><strong> </strong>Welcome to <strong>Sprint #2</strong> of <strong><a href="https://www.meetup.com/bostonphp/events/294062551/">API a la Mode, Season 3</a></strong>. Let's continue.</p>
<p>This sprint will last one week and will cover the second of three units in the <strong><a href="https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/apis-for-beginners/">APIs for Beginners Tutorial</a></strong>—a free course offered by freeCodeCamp.</p>
<p><strong>Scorecard</strong><br /><br /><span>~ Seven members signed up for Season 3</span><br /><span>~ Three members made the commitment to begin<br />~ One member completed Season 3<br /></span>~ Two additional members completed Sprint #1</p>
<p>If you have not yet done so, please post a brief update to <strong><a href="https://www.meetup.com/bostonphp/messages/boards/thread/53905621/">Introduce Yourself</a></strong> which will acknowledge your commitment to begin this training opportunity. Next, we will conduct three sprints over the next three weeks to complete the three units in this video-based training.</p>
<p><strong>Sprint #2</strong> covers <strong>Exploring APIs</strong>. This second of three sprints began on June 26 and concludes on July 2, 2023. Once you complete this one-hour unit, please post an update at <strong><a href="https://www.meetup.com/bostonphp/messages/boards/thread/53914428">Sprint #2—API a la Mode, Season 3</a></strong> so that I can monitor participant progress. Then, proceed to the next unit in this three-hour video.</p>
<p>Links to all discussions are posted at <strong><a href="https://www.meetup.com/bostonphp/messages/boards/thread/53905614">Master Discussion List</a>.</strong></p>
<p>Let's continue interfacing (virtually, of course).</p>
